abstract: Attention turns fully to November, and Biden admits a “gut punch.” This is your morning tip sheet.
snippet: Attention turns fully to November, and Biden admits a “gut punch.” This is your morning tip sheet.
lead_paragraph: Andrew Yang after an event in Keene, N.H., on Wednesday. He is trying to appeal directly to New Hampshire voters who supported Donald J. Trump in 2016 and are now looking for a Democrat to woo them.

abstract: You’ve definitively shown us why you shouldn’t be first on the political calendar, and so much more.
snippet: You’ve definitively shown us why you shouldn’t be first on the political calendar, and so much more.
lead_paragraph: As Iowa Democrats struggle to tally votes and claw their way out of the rubble of Monday’s caucus crackup, there continues to be angst and outrage about the damage the Hawkeye State has inflicted on the democratic process — and the Democratic process. Terms like “catastrophe,” “debacle,” “fiasco” and “disaster” are being tossed about like salad greens.

abstract: The approach is not to appear more ethical than the other candidate but to tear down that person’s character.
snippet: The approach is not to appear more ethical than the other candidate but to tear down that person’s character.
lead_paragraph: Given the amount of political news being generated these days, you could be forgiven for not paying close attention to both the Trump-Ukraine scandal and the 2020 presidential campaign. But they are actually one and the same: The scandal is the campaign.

abstract: On a private conference call, Iowa Democratic leaders revealed more about how the reporting process on Monday night went calamitously awry.
snippet: On a private conference call, Iowa Democratic leaders revealed more about how the reporting process on Monday night went calamitously awry.
lead_paragraph: Iowa Democratic officials said on a private conference call on Wednesday night that nearly all the much-delayed results of Monday’s caucuses would be released by Thursday, although a few precincts might remain outstanding.

headline_main: Snail Mail and Nuisance Calls: New Details on the Iowa Caucus Problems
byline_original: By Trip Gabriel and Reid J. Epstein

abstract: Mr. Biden has gone on the offensive, taking aim at two rivals ahead of him in the Iowa results, Pete Buttigieg and Bernie Sanders, while Ms. Warren continues to stress unity.
snippet: Mr. Biden has gone on the offensive, taking aim at two rivals ahead of him in the Iowa results, Pete Buttigieg and Bernie Sanders, while Ms. Warren continues to stress unity.
lead_paragraph: MANCHESTER, N.H. — Joseph R. Biden Jr. and Senator Elizabeth Warren each suffered a damaging setback in Iowa that could make it harder for them to recover next week in New Hampshire — and not just because they were running well behind the leading candidates as Democrats awaited a final count.

abstract: The growing extremism of the debate alienates many people on the left and right.
snippet: The growing extremism of the debate alienates many people on the left and right.
lead_paragraph: Where will abortion opponents stand in 2020? President Trump recently made his bid for their votes, becoming the first president to speak in person at the annual March for Life in Washington, an event held since 1974. Two days later, a Democratic presidential hopeful, Pete Buttigieg, told a woman who called herself a “proud pro-life Democrat” that he would not support more moderate abortion language in the Democratic National Committee platform — basically suggesting that, on this issue, she will not find affirmation or support from her party.
